If you want to rip multiple titles (as in a DVD with multiple TV episodes), select 1 title, give it a unique name in the File Area and click Add to Queue. Repeat the process until you've added all desired titles to your encoding queue. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e7/13b2.jpg/v4-460px-13b2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/e7/13b2.jpg/v4-760px-13b2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
